It was part of what you did, and you hated it, you hated your vagina for working so perfectly and you hated how you got caught and now spend your days with the Knight family.

The man had raped the girl in his house, and, apparently, the only people that can rape the Handmaids were the men of the house, so he was sentenced to death by physical abuse. You followed the girls who circled around him and watched as they started to hit him. You pretended to throw a few punches and kick but you didn’t actually touch him. You stayed your distance and left the other girls to do so.

“Thank you, girls, you may now leave,” Aunt Lydia spoke, her glare fixed onto all the girls as they left.

You found your partner, a very quite girl called Ofnick, but, you two were the perfect pair because the two of you didn’t speak much. You greeted each other, you walked, you left. That’s all you two do together, but, if your honest, you can’t wait to leave her and be alone. But you’re never really alone in this place.

You walk into the house, take your robe and hat off and walking into the kitchen where Florence the maid was making your lunch and Harry was sat eating his lunch, “Blessed be the fruit.”

“May the lord open,” Florence says whilst Harry nods his head in your direction. Completely professional.

Everybody spoils you on this day, since it’s the ceremony, the whole reason that you’re here being a handmaid is because of today, and hopefully the life you will possess because of it. Harry can’t look you in the eye on the day of the ceremony, and you get why, but sometimes it hurts. You need him on these days and he can’t even look you in the eye.

The second you sit down and start to eat, Harry passes his plate to Florence and leaves. You don’t let it show, but it hurts, so to mask it, you try to eat as much of the food as possibly before going upstairs. Mrs Knight makes it clear that she wants everything perfect on the night of the ceremony and that includes you taking a special bath, with the sweet scented shower gels and shampoos.

The door to the bathroom doesn’t have a lock, and it’s not like you can take a bath naked, and if you’re honest, everybody in the house has seen you naked apart from Florence. There’s no privacy when you’re a Handmaid, you do what you do and you let everybody else have reigns on your life. The bath is supposed to be relaxing, but it’s not. Not on ceremony day.

You hated when there was a meeting with all the Handmaids and Aunt Lydia, since it normally meant that somebody had committed a crime and you would have to punish them. It was part of what you did, and you hated it, you hated your vagina for working so perfectly and you hated how you got caught and now spend your days with the Knight family.

The man had raped the girl in his house, and, apparently, the only people that can rape the Handmaids were the men of the house, so he was sentenced to death by physical abuse. You followed the girls who circled around him and watched as they started to hit him. You pretended to throw a few punches and kick but you didn’t actually touch him. You stayed your distance and left the other girls to do so.

“Thank you, girls, you may now leave,” Aunt Lydia spoke, her glare fixed onto all the girls as they left.

You found your partner, a very quite girl called Ofnick, but, you two were the perfect pair because the two of you didn’t speak much. You greeted each other, you walked, you left. That’s all you two do together, but, if your honest, you can’t wait to leave her and be alone. But you’re never really alone in this place.

You walk into the house, take your robe and hat off and walking into the kitchen where Florence the maid was making your lunch and Harry was sat eating his lunch, “Blessed be the fruit.”

“May the lord open,” Florence says whilst Harry nods his head in your direction. Completely professional.

Everybody spoils you on this day, since it’s the ceremony, the whole reason that you’re here being a handmaid is because of today, and hopefully the life you will possess because of it. Harry can’t look you in the eye on the day of the ceremony, and you get why, but sometimes it hurts. You need him on these days and he can’t even look you in the eye.

The second you sit down and start to eat, Harry passes his plate to Florence and leaves. You don’t let it show, but it hurts, so to mask it, you try to eat as much of the food as possibly before going upstairs. Mrs Knight makes it clear that she wants everything perfect on the night of the ceremony and that includes you taking a special bath, with the sweet scented shower gels and shampoos.

The door to the bathroom doesn’t have a lock, and it’s not like you can take a bath naked, and if you’re honest, everybody in the house has seen you naked apart from Florence. There’s no privacy when you’re a Handmaid, you do what you do and you let everybody else have reigns on your life. The bath is supposed to be relaxing, but it’s not. Not on ceremony day.

Mr Knight had to knock before he could enter the room, and once he entered, the ceremony would start. You would have to kneel there, with Harry stood behind you, and listen to Mr Knights voice as he reads from the ceremony book.

You still feel his touch way after it’s done, and you still feel him inside of you, but you just ignore it. You don’t want this to happen, but there’s nothing you can do. Not until Harry gets you away from here in the next week. title: The Gravity of Everything
body:
She was the keeper of their dream. An answered prayer. Someone who came into their life at exactly the right time. Who knew they would ever find themselves in this situation in this first place?

Because Harry Styles may be a lot of things in this world, may be the most famous, have the best things money could buy, but even he couldn’t fix the fact that Jess couldn’t have a baby.

For someone who seems to have everything, for all the dreams he’s ever dreamt and ones that have already come true, the one thing he wanted the most kept eluding him.

Until her.

It was because of her that his dream was coming true. Their dream. He knows he’s in love with Jess. He’s happy with their lives as it is and a baby would just make their lives so much better. So why is he all of a sudden curious about this other woman carrying his child?

The Gravity of Everything is a story of how sometimes the very thing we’re hoping and praying for can also be our undoing. How do you choose between what you know you should do and what your heart wants to do?

AAAAHHH IT’S FINALLY HERE! This story came to me in the wee hours of the morning in my jetlagged, can’t sleep state. I wanted to write something different. A story so beyond my wildest dreams, one that wasn’t as restricted to timelines and real life as The Secret Girlfriend Series. 

The Gravity of Everything is a love story at its core, but also a story about being human. Nothing is face value in this world, and i hope that through this I get to explore emotions and motivations and all its complexities. I’m super excited to work on this fic! I hope you are too. 

Also I’m still struggling with what to call the other woman in the story? Please let me know your name suggestions here. First chapter will be up very soon xx Anna
